Description: Dual phase-distortion synthesiser with CZ-style oscillator engine, fixed-level oscillator 2 detune for external mixing, hardware-tested 1V/oct pitch input, matched CV modulation in synth and Turing modes, mode-specific knob pickup, envelope presets, Web MIDI editing, USB MIDI, manual flash persistence, and a self-playing probabilistic Turing machine sequencer.
Name: C1ZZL3
Language: C++ (Pico SDK)
Creator: Adrian Vos
Instagram: https://instagram.com/professeur_whom
Version: 0.6
Status: Hardware-tested working

tags:
  - synthesiser
  - phase-distortion
  - oscillator
  - turing-machine
  - sequencer
  - envelope
  - 1v-oct

manual: |
  C1ZZL3 is a CZ-inspired phase-distortion oscillator card with a second mirrored oscillator for
  fixed-level detune, ring modulation, and CZ-style noise/grit. Audio/CV in 1 tracks at a
  hardware-tested 1V/oct scale. CV In 1 modulates phase-distortion amount and CV In 2 modulates
  waveform morph in both synth and Turing modes.

  Switch middle is the main PD synth voice. Hold the switch down from middle to edit the latched
  second oscillator, ring modulation, and grit controls using soft pickup. Hold down for 8 seconds
  to save those latched settings to flash. There is no autosave. Main, X, and Y also use
  mode-specific pickup when switching between synth and Turing modes, so stored values do not jump
  until the physical knob is moved back through its stored value.

  Switch up opens the Turing machine. It outputs stepped and smoothed Turing CV, two Turing pulse
  streams, and a self-playing stepped oscillator voice using the last PD synth sound. The Turing
  CV and pulse outputs continue running in synth mode from the last Turing settings. If an envelope
  preset is active, the main Turing pulse self-triggers the envelope without oscillator sync.

  Hold the switch down during startup to enter envelope preset select. Release the startup hold,
  use Main to choose preset 0-8, short-press down to exit, or long-hold down to save the preset.

panel:
  inputs:
    - id: AudioIn1
      name: Audio/CV In 1
      description: 1V/oct pitch modulation in PD synth mode
    - id: AudioIn2
      name: Audio/CV In 2
      description: Currently unused
    - id: CVIn1
      name: CV In 1
      description: Phase-distortion amount modulation in PD synth and Turing modes
    - id: CVIn2
      name: CV In 2
      description: Waveform morph modulation in PD synth and Turing modes
    - id: PulseIn1
      name: Pulse In 1
      description: External Turing clock in switch-up mode
    - id: PulseIn2
      name: Pulse In 2
      description: Triggers the selected envelope preset and softened oscillator sync in PD synth mode when preset 1-8 is active; preset 0 ignores Pulse In 2
  outputs:
    - id: AudioOut1
      name: Audio Out 1
      description: Oscillator 1 in PD synth mode; self-playing stepped oscillator 1 in Turing mode
    - id: AudioOut2
      name: Audio Out 2
      description: Oscillator 2 in PD synth mode; self-playing stepped oscillator 2 in Turing mode
    - id: CVOut1
      name: CV Out 1
      description: Scaled stepped Turing CV
    - id: CVOut2
      name: CV Out 2
      description: Smoothed scaled Turing CV
    - id: PulseOut1
      name: Pulse Out 1
      description: Main Turing pulse
    - id: PulseOut2
      name: Pulse Out 2
      description: Alternate Turing bit pulse

controls:
  knobs:
    - when: { z: middle }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Oscillator pitch over octave-based range; uses mode-specific pickup when returning from Turing mode
      x:
        name: X
        description: Phase-distortion amount; CV In 1 modulates the same parameter; uses mode-specific pickup when returning from Turing mode
      y:
        name: Y
        description: Waveform morph across saw, square, pulse, double sine, saw-pulse curve, and three CZ-style resonance-window waveforms; CV In 2 modulates the same parameter; uses mode-specific pickup when returning from Turing mode

    - when: { z: down, gesture: hold }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Latched oscillator 2 detune from centre at fixed output level; normal pitch is held while editing
      x:
        name: X
        description: Latched ring modulation amount; uses soft pickup
      y:
        name: Y
        description: Latched CZ-style noise/grit amount; uses soft pickup

    - when: { z: up }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Turing mutation/lock amount; centre is most random and extremes are more locked; uses mode-specific pickup when returning from synth mode
      x:
        name: X
        description: Turing sequence length, 2 to 16 steps; uses mode-specific pickup when returning from synth mode
      y:
        name: Y
        description: Internal Turing clock speed; uses mode-specific pickup when returning from synth mode

    - when: { z: up, gesture: flick-down }
      main:
        name: Switch Down
        description: Tap internal Turing clock tempo

    - when: { startup: switch-down }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Select envelope preset 0-8
      switch:
        name: Switch Down
        description: Short press exits preset select; long hold saves selected preset to flash

  leds:
    - when: { z: middle }
      display: list
      items:
        - id: LED0
          name: LED 0
          description: Phase-distortion amount
        - id: LED1
          name: LED 1
          description: Waveform morph position
        - id: LED2
          name: LED 2
          description: Oscillator 2 detune amount
        - id: LED3
          name: LED 3
          description: Ring modulation amount
        - id: LED4
          name: LED 4
          description: Noise/grit amount
        - id: LED5
          name: LED 5
          description: Lights while switch is held down

    - when: { z: up }
      display: list
      items:
        - id: LED0
          name: LED 0
          description: Low bit 0 of Turing pattern
        - id: LED1
          name: LED 1
          description: Low bit 1 of Turing pattern
        - id: LED2
          name: LED 2
          description: Low bit 2 of Turing pattern
        - id: LED3
          name: LED 3
          description: Pulse In 1 state
        - id: LED4
          name: LED 4
          description: Turing sequence length
        - id: LED5
          name: LED 5
          description: Flashes on every Turing clock step

    - when: { startup: envelope-select }
      display: binary
      items:
        - id: LED0
          name: LED 0
          description: Envelope preset binary bit 0
        - id: LED1
          name: LED 1
          description: Envelope preset binary bit 1
        - id: LED2
          name: LED 2
          description: Envelope preset binary bit 2
        - id: LED3
          name: LED 3
          description: Envelope preset binary bit 3
        - id: LED4
          name: LED 4
          description: Envelope preset binary bit 4
        - id: LED5
          name: LED 5
          description: Envelope preset binary bit 5

presets:
  waveforms:
    - id: 1
      name: Saw
      description: Saw-tooth phase-distortion target
    - id: 2
      name: Square
      description: Square phase-distortion target
    - id: 3
      name: Needle pulse
      description: Narrow pulse phase-distortion target
    - id: 4
      name: Double sine
      description: Double-sine phase-distortion target
    - id: 5
      name: Saw-pulse curve
      description: Curved saw-pulse phase-distortion target
    - id: 6
      name: Resonance I, saw window
      description: Saw-windowed resonant waveform
    - id: 7
      name: Resonance II, triangle window
      description: Triangle-windowed resonant waveform
    - id: 8
      name: Resonance III, trapezoid window
      description: Trapezoid-windowed resonant waveform

  envelopes:
    - id: 0
      name: Off
      description: Free-running oscillator; Pulse In 2 is ignored
    - id: 1
      name: Pluck
      description: Fast plucked envelope
    - id: 2
      name: Double pluck
      description: Two plucked attacks in one envelope
    - id: 3
      name: Bounce
      description: Multi-stage bouncing drop-and-rise envelope
    - id: 4
      name: Bell
      description: Bright bell-like envelope
    - id: 5
      name: Brass
      description: Slower brass-style envelope
    - id: 6
      name: Strings
      description: Multi-stage strings-style envelope
    - id: 7
      name: Reverse swell
      description: Reverse swell with late peak
    - id: 8
      name: Evolving digital
      description: Multi-stage amp and phase-distortion movement
